Scallop Petroleum Corp, a subsidiaryof Royal Dutch/Shell group, said today it raised contractprices for heavy fuel 25 cts to 1.75 dlrs a barrel, effectivetoday.    The increase brings the price for 0.3 pct sulphur to 22.50dlrs, up 1.75, 0.5 pct sulphur to 21.50 dlrs, up 1.50, 0.7 pctsulphur to 20.25 dlrs, up 75 cts, one pct sulphur to 19.50dlrs, up 25 cts, two pct sulphur to 18.75 dlrs, up 75 cts, 2.2pct sulphur to 18.50 dlrs, up 75 cts, 2.8 pct sulphur to 18.00dlrs, up 75 cts. Reuter&#3;